721267f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 34th Street (East)
721267f-a.text:
197 to 185 Madison Ave., east side, south from East 35th to 34th
Streets, showing a row of houses, Nos. 197 to 189, that will be demolished
and the site improved by a 14-story apartment house, to be known as
No. 20 East 35th Street. This new structure will occupy the entire upper
portion of this block front exclusive of the N.E. corner of East 34th
Street where upon stands the 16estory Cameron Building, No. 195. For
further data see, the New York Times -- October 14, 1937, Page 46L.
September 15, 1937.
George D. Chinn.

721266f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 34th Street (East)
721266f-a.text:
Madison Ave., east side, north from East 34th to 37th Streets, showing
in the foreground a row of 4-story houses (Nos. 189-197) that will be
replaced by a 14-story apartment house. On the N.E. corner of East 35th
Street, appears the Church of the Incarnation. Occupying the 36th to
37th block is the J. P. Morgan home and Library.
September 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
